  <main>
    <header class="article-header">
      <div class="article-header-cat">Methodology</div>
      <h1>How we review</h1>
      <div class="article-header-meta">
        <span>Last updated: April 2026</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">
      <p>Every product recommendation on this site follows a consistent process. Here's exactly how we research, evaluate, and publish.</p>

      <h2>Research first</h2>
      <p>Before testing or recommending any product, we research it thoroughly. This means reading the peer-reviewed literature on the underlying technology (HRV measurement, photobiomodulation, cold exposure protocols), reviewing published accuracy studies, and cross-referencing manufacturer claims against independent findings.</p>

      <p>We cite sources. If a claim isn't backed by evidence, it doesn't appear on this site.</p>

      <h2>Hands-on testing where possible</h2>
      <p>For sleep trackers and wearables, we test products personally over a minimum of 30 nights before publishing conclusions. Where we have used a product personally, we say so explicitly and provide real data where relevant (sleep scores, HRV readings, accuracy comparisons).</p>

      <p>For products we haven't personally tested — supplements we haven't trialled, red light panels we don't own — we rely on published research, verified user data from communities including r/ouraring and r/biohacking, and third-party accuracy studies. We are transparent about this distinction.</p>

      <h2>Scoring and comparison</h2>
      <p>We do not use a numeric rating system. Numeric scores suggest false precision — an 8.7 vs 8.9 tells you nothing meaningful. Instead, we give a clear verdict: who a product is right for, who should skip it, and what the specific trade-offs are.</p>

      <h2>Update cadence</h2>
      <p>Sleep tracker firmware changes frequently. Supplement research evolves. Prices shift. We review and update our buying guides at least every 6 months, and immediately when a significant product change warrants it. The "Updated" date on every article reflects when the content was materially revised — not just corrected for typos.</p>

      <h2>Affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>We earn commissions from some of the links on this site. These relationships do not influence our editorial conclusions. Full details at our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a> page.</p>

      <h2>What we won't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Fabricate product specifications, sensor accuracy data, or user experience</li>
        <li>Rank a product higher because it pays a higher commission</li>
        <li>Accept payment for editorial coverage or positive reviews</li>
        <li>Make medical claims about products we review</li>
      </ul>

      <p>If you spot an error or have evidence that contradicts something we've published, please <a href="/contact/">let us know</a>. We correct mistakes quickly and transparently.</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
